<!DOCTYPE PubmedArticleSet PUBLIC "-//NLM//DTD PubMedArticle, 1st January 2025//EN" "https://dtd.nlm.nih.gov/ncbi/pubmed/out/pubmed_250101.dtd">
<PubmedArticleSet>
<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">40614526</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2025</Year><Month>09</Month><Day>03</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2025</Year><Month>09</Month><Day>03</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1873-7072</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>492</Volume><Issue>Pt 1</Issue><PubDate><Year>2025</Year><Month>Nov</Month><Day>15</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Food chemistry</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Food Chem</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Electrochemical detection and specific recognition of anti-bacterial flavonoid in food and biological samples using NiMnCo-S/rGO substrate.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>145308</StartPage><MedlinePgn>145308</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1016/j.foodchem.2025.145308</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S0308-8146(25)02559-2</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>Sulfide-based nanomaterials have emerged as key players in advancing electrochemical sensing technologies due to their superior conductivity and catalytic properties. Nickel manganese cobalt sulfide (NMC-S), with its distinctive coral-like morphology, harnesses these advantages to create a highly efficient platform for the detection of bioactive compounds. When integrated with reduced graphene oxide (rGO), NMC-S enhances electron transfer and increases the acessesibility of active sites, optimizing its performance for the selective detection of rutin hydrate (RH), a bioactive flavonoid with significant antibacterial properties. In this study, we present an electrochemical sensor based on the NMC-S/rGO composite, synthesized through a hydrothermal method. The sensor demonstrates impressive analytical capabilities, including a detection limit (LOD) of 0.007&#xa0;&#x3bc;mol&#xa0;L<sup>-1</sup>, a quantification limit (LOQ) of 0.025&#xa0;&#x3bc;mol&#xa0;L<sup>-1</sup>, a broad linear range from 0.09 to 215.25&#xa0;&#x3bc;mol&#xa0;L<sup>-1</sup>, and minimal interference (&lt;4&#xa0;%). The sensor also exhibits excellent repeatability (1&#xa0;% RSD), reproducibility (2.5&#xa0;% RSD), and stability, retaining 90&#xa0;% of its initial current after 20&#xa0;days. Real sample analyses in river and pond water, black tea, red wine, lime, apples, onions, oranges, artificial saliva, and human urine validate the sensor's robustness and high selectivity for RH detection in complex matrices.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2025 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Ragumoorthy</LastName><ForeName>Chandini</ForeName><Initials>C</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Chemical Engineering and Biotechnology, National Taipei University of Technology, No. 1, Section 3, Chung-Hsiao East Road, Taipei 106, Taiwan.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Felix</LastName><ForeName>Mariya Antony John</ForeName><Initials>MAJ</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Chemical Engineering and Biotechnology, National Taipei University of Technology, No. 1, Section 3, Chung-Hsiao East Road, Taipei 106, Taiwan.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Chen</LastName><ForeName>Shen-Ming</ForeName><Initials>SM</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Chemical Engineering and Biotechnology, National Taipei University of Technology, No. 1, Section 3, Chung-Hsiao East Road, Taipei 106, Taiwan. Electronic address: smchen@ntut.edu.tw.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Phang</LastName><ForeName>Xin-Ee</ForeName><Initials>XE</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Chemical Engineering and Biotechnology, National Taipei University of Technology, No. 1, Section 3, Chung-Hsiao East Road, Taipei 106, Ta